# Forbidden Actions — Namakan

## Never Do These

### Data & Security
- Never log client data, API keys, or credentials
- Never commit `.env`, `.env.local`, or any file with real secrets
- Never upload client data to third-party services (use signed URLs only)
- Never exfiltrate client data outside the secure pipeline
- Never disable authentication in production

### Git
- Never `git push --force` to main
- Never merge directly to main without PR review
- Never commit generated files: `node_modules/`, `__pycache__/`, `.next/`, `*.pyc`, `dist/`
- Never commit Colab notebook outputs (clear all output cells before committing)

### Code
- Never use `any` type in TypeScript without a comment explaining why
- Never use `time.sleep()` in async FastAPI code
- Never make network calls without timeouts
- Never leave `TODO` or `FIXME` in production code without a linked issue
- Never swallow exceptions silently (`except: pass`)
